        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-07-31T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-07-31T04:00:00-05:00" n="1319" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1319">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1115/7–3149: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister-Counselor of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Clark</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Canton</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-07-31T17:00:00+08:00">July 31, 1949—5 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received August 3—2:12 p. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Cantel 858. Local managers SVOC and Caltex inform us just received instructions
                    from New York liquidate offices and evacuate entire American staff before
                    Communist takeover, Cantel 845, July 28, repeated Nanking 560, Shanghai 467.
                    SVOC has estimated $200,000 stock, Caltex $500,000. Plan unload fastest possible
                    begin evacuation some staff within few days, then gradually reduce until final
                    withdrawal.</p>
                <p>SVOC plans put committee Chinese employees in charge property. Caltex working out
                    details. Both expect seek assistance evacuation some equipment.</p>
                <p>Sent Department Cantel 858; repeated Nanking 566, Shanghai 473.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Clark</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
